COPS in Limpopo
have open docket after an elephant has trampled and killed a ranger in Hlomela
village outside Giyani. Cops spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the there
were loose elephants at Hlomela Village which were spotted by the Community near
the Kruger National park. The rangers who were tracing the two elephants shot one
dead but the other attacked and killed Masenyane Thomas Makhubele (59). The deceased was  residing
in Giyani section E. The deceased was a Ranger at the Kruger National Park. Ngoepe said the 
investigations continue.